Local star Connor Buck defended his title, winning the men’s elite race in 17 minutes and 39 seconds. #dstv403 HOWICK - The 50th edition of the Midmar Mile open water race featured a star-studded field in Howick. Netherlands star Sharon Van Rouwendaal won the women's race in 18 minutes and 40 seconds. She was followed closely by American Ashley Twichel from the USA. Local star Connor Buck defended his title, winning the men’s elite race in 17 minutes and 39 seconds. Henre Louwe was second with Brendan Visser completing the podium.